# Newspaper UI Modernization Rules

This project is a static Bangla-first newspaper UI prototype. Improve UI/UX only unless the user explicitly asks for backend or framework work.

## Must Keep
- Keep `index.html` as the preview entry point.
- Keep the app static and dependency-free.
- Keep Bangla/English language toggle working.
- Keep `window.KHOBOR_DATA` as the content source.
- Keep dynamic rendering safe by escaping user/content values.

## Do Not Do
- Do not add React, Vue, Next.js, Laravel, Vite, Tailwind, npm, composer, database, API, or backend code.
- Do not replace the whole project structure unless explicitly asked.
- Do not remove existing fonts or design-token files.
- Do not make the design look like a generic blog template.

## UI Direction
Create a premium Bangladeshi news portal experience:
- editorial
- trustworthy
- modern
- responsive
- Bangla-first
- fast and lightweight

Use polished colors, refined spacing, modern cards, better typography, useful icons, subtle animations, and strong mobile UX.

## Required Quality
- Write clear section comments in CSS.
- Write concise comments for major JS render helpers and interaction handlers.
- Use semantic HTML.
- Add accessible names to icon buttons.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Test desktop, tablet, and mobile layouts mentally before finalizing changes.
